comment: We have made it to Vilnius! Starting the holiday with a homemade kvass. Sweet and sour with bonus floating raisins.

This is the best Kvass I have had so far in Poland and Lithuania. It is homemade here at the restaurant from dark, rustic rye bread, and you can taste the rye bread. Lightly tart and sweet. Bready. Served with a few white cranberries floating on top.
